\frac{dy}{dx} = y^2 + 2xy - 3x^2 + 1
y*
Y = y - y*
y* = x
Y = y - x
Y = y - x => y = Y + x
\frac{dy}{dx} = y^2 + 2xy - 3x^2 + 1
y = Y + x
\frac{d(Y+x)}{dx} = (Y+x)^2 + 2x(Y+x) - 3x^2 + 1
\frac{dY}{dx} = Y^2 + 4xY
u = \frac{1}{Y}
\frac{du}{dx} + 4xu = -1 
u = \frac{-1}{4}
u = e^{-4x} - 1
\frac{dy}{dx} = Y^2 + 4xY
u = \frac{1}{Y}
\frac{du}{dx} + 4u = -1 
u
\frac{du}{dx} + 4u = 0
u=c e^{-4 x}
\frac{du}{dx} + 4u = 1
u=c e^{-4 x}-\frac{1}{4}
c=0
c=1
